**He sits up suddenly.** "Am I alive? Did I make it, chief?"

"Alfred! I- I was locked horns with the Wyrd before I fell asleep! I just had him, too! Are you aware of his whereabouts, or the whereabouts of Guy Fucks?"
(sorry it's been like 2 and a half months It's hard to remember what the fuck was happening lol)
Alfred sighs. "I don't know who either of---" He shakes his head. "Whoever was near you when you passed out is gone, I think. Witness testimony is sparse."

"Gragh! I've been damned!" **He looks down and shakes his head.** "I apologize Alfred, that bout was one I deemed important, but that opportunity has passed me by... how are you, Alfred? What brings you to Imperva?"
"All hands on deck for the latest crisis." He sighs. "The whole Eulogia thing. You're aware of part of it. ZTD'll probably be ready for use by tomorrow."
**He nods.** "That's fantastic! I'm grateful for the opportunity to be a help, although I am worried what effect I'll have, peering into the brain of a poor sick girl..."

"I don't think this is a comfort, but I doubt you can make things worse." Alfred closes his book and looks down on his lap. "There's... a lot riding on this. I'd make sure you're ready for it. Physically. I have full faith in you there. But also mentally. If there's anything you want to get done, take your mind off of it and deal with it today. We need everyone involved to be as focused as possible for this."
**He nods his head.** "Yeah. I've..."
"The last few days haven't been easy, Alfred. I appreciate it."
**He cracks his neck.** "How much time would it take to get to Burdlt and back? I have a couple people I need to talk to there..."
"You should be able to go there and be back in time if [DIRECTIONS]." He says.

**He stands up.** "Thanks, Alfred." **He walks to the door steadily.** "Alfred... I think something is going to happen soon. I can't... I can't describe exactly what it is or what it will be, but I think everything is going to change. So... get ready."
"That's..." He chuckles. "I guess I can't call you overly ominous after what I just dropped on you. I'll be cautious. We've both been through more than enough, in our own ways. This won't stop us."
**He nods at Alfred.** "You will find a way forward, I'm sure of it! There is more to your story I have yet to bear witness to. I'll see you tomorrow, friend!"
**He leaves and begins the trek to Burdlt unless someone stops him.**

"The crown. That's a bit abstract. More specifically: A man who goes by 'TGP'."
"How did you come into contact with this individual?"

He thinks for a moment. "I don't quite remember. It was a long chain of associates asking me to check on other people, eventually leading to a note placed for me to read with instructions. Oh! The penultimate one before TGP... I don't know, he was sort of an unpleasant, vermin-like man? I can't remember the name."
"...Unpleasant, vermin-like... hmph. How did you end up in Arctica, Marshland?"
"I don't... understand the question. I was born here."
"So you *are* truly a federal agent? Why have you allowed yourself to be caught?"
"I've thought about my situation for a long time, and I'm beginning to think I may have been betrayed by my country. I'm happy they didn't think of killing me so I didn't talk, at least."
"You were personally employed by the crown to facilitate their plans, and then discarded?"
"Yes. I suppose."
"Do you regret it?"
"Hm. Hard to say. I still believe what I was doing was for the best. But I'd rather not be here, yeah."
"...Do you think you're a good person, Marshland?"
"I suppose so."
**MBMJ nods to himself. He steps outside to speak to Jennica.** "Excuse me, Marshland is currently detained because of what he did to me, correct?"
"That's the primary thing. He really should've received a more proper verdict by now, but everything's kind of been a shitshow lately."

"...Well, I'd like to make a statement about that day. At around that time, Hirer Dreng was impersonating me, wearing a suit that looked alarmingly like mine. He was taking the opportunity to commit crimes, and act with criminal malfeasance. I believe it is possible, even probable, that Marshland was made aware of someone in my visage committing wrongdoings, and then chose to intervene when he saw me, seeking to heroically subdue me with as little violence as possible to provide succor for his fantasies. 

I cannot speak on his other crimes, but I do not believe he should continue to be locked up for that infraction."

"Pbbbbbb." Jennica makes a weird mouth noise. "Well, I guess so. Can't guarantee we won't come after him again if new info shows up, but you've gained enough trust with me that I'll take your word. I'll get the process to release him started."
**MBMJ nods at her.** "Let me know if there's anything else... I should do. I've recently been gifted with a lot more free time."
"You know how to contact me."
She nods. "Have a nice day."
**He exits and then heads to the AWF headquarters, holding his breath.**
The AWF headquarters are reached. Beloved character The Early Bird is there, but in like, normal clothes, seemingly on his way out. He nods at you.
"...Is it bad?"

"I don't quite know. Selfish as it may be, I'm taking measures to be less ruined if things turn for the worst. I'll remain as long as I can." He points over to a room. "Walter would have the most up to date information."
"...It's no problem, Bird. Everybody's got to take care of themselves. Thank you for laboring to remain." **MBMJ walks to meet Walter.**
Walter is in his office. "Erm, hello." The non-character waves. "Good to, uh, see you."
"Hello Walter. I've been... absent recently, I'm afraid."
"Have things been significantly changed by... what happened in the capitol?"

"Mmm. I've received a lot of threatening notices. Lot of budgetary cuts. I don't know how exactly things will pan out, but it doesn't look... good." He sighs. 

"The chieftain of the province wants to assume direct control of the AWF. He's threatening to stop most of our income flow if I don't. I'm not so self-centered that I need to keep this position, but he worries me."
**MBMJ buries his face in his hands.** "I... You're going away? But you didn't do anything? It wasn't your fault!"
"No, I'll stay around here. Try to take up some other role in the company. Things just... have to change. It's our best shot to survive."
**MBMJ scratches his shoulder.** "...We've been through worse, right?"

"Y-um--well... No, not really. I don't mean to remove hope, but I think this probably is literally the worst it has gotten." He sighs.

"Still. We've got a lot of talented people here. We'll figure something out. Wish Bruna was back... but I guess I'm glad she's still away. She'd be devastated by all this."
**MBMJ rolls his shoulders and lets out a wry breath. He slumps down in his chair.** "Oh... oh no... why..."
**He puts his head down.**
"Er-uh... I don't... there there. It's probably fine..." Walter struggles to express anything at all.
"Can I... can I... do anything? Is there? Is there a quest for me?"
He puts his finger on his chin, then produces an envelope from his desk drawer. "Could you deliver this to a man named Virtos Dextrum? It'd be better if I stay here."
"Y-yeah. I can do that."
